
The Royal College of Physicians is offering 8 International Bursaries in 2006 for physicians practising in low-income and lower-middle-income countries* for attendance at an RCP conference in the UK, and a 2-4 week study visit to a relevant specialist unit. The aim of the new RCP Bursaries is to enable talented and motivated young physicians to have access to a quality post-graduate educational experience to stimulate their learning, and encourage them to share good practice and knowledge on their return home... click link for more info.

